The paper introduces a software platform for dialog research, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The platform also involves machine learning models, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely sub-category. The platform's goal of improving upon existing architectures and integrating human evaluation suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible sub-category. The platform also involves human-computer interaction (HCI) through the integration of Amazon Mechanical Turk, which suggests cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the platform supports several tasks related to question answering and information retrieval, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
